# Tests that @test(eq, EXPR) expected expressions may reference builtins gated
# behind a per-file @experiment(...) attribute. The expected expression is a
# builtin call, so it is routed through cmpBuiltinExpr; that compiles it within
# a synthetic file carrying the file's @experiment(reflect) prefix (and matching
# language version), so a reflect validator such as validN compiles and compares
# against the value.
#
# Without this, the expected expression would be compiled in a bare context and
# the run would fail with:
#   cannot compile expression validN(...): builtin "validN" requires
#   @experiment(reflect)
-- in/test.cue --
@experiment(reflect)

a: 1
b: 2

// The validator built from references equals the same builtin call written
// with literal arguments. The expected expression compiles only because the
// file enables @experiment(reflect).
v: validN(>=1, a, b) @test(eq, validN(>=1, 1, 2))
-- out/status.txt --
update: identical to input
force:  identical to update
